#: ../../talk/federation_index.rst:2
msgid "Federation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/federation_index.rst:4
msgid "With the Federation feature, users can create conversations across different federated Talk instances and use Talk features as if they were on the same server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/federation_index.rst:6
msgid "This feature must be enabled by a system administrator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/federation_index.rst:9
msgid "Sending an invitation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/federation_index.rst:11
msgid "To receive an invitation, the other party needs your CloudID. You can find your CloudID in **Personal settings** under **Sharing** — it looks like ``user@cloud.example.com``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/federation_index.rst:13
msgid "The moderator of the conversation can send an invite to a participant on a different server:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/federation_index.rst:19
msgid "Accepting an invitation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/federation_index.rst:21
msgid "When receiving a notification, the user will see a counter of pending invites above the conversations list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/federation_index.rst:26
msgid "Upon clicking it, more information will be provided about the inviting party, and the user can either accept or decline the invitation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/federation_index.rst:31
msgid "By accepting the invite, the conversation will appear in the list as any other one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/federation_index.rst:36
msgid "You can use it to chat with participants from other federated servers, join calls, and use other available Talk features."
msgstr ""
